        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down. | Bromley. | Kent. S.E.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>Sep 2. 1868 </date>
                    <salute>My dear Thwaites</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I am very much obliged to you for taking all my questions so very kindly &amp; pleasantly.<ref target="#foot.f1"/> You have indeed entered on the fowl question in real earnest &amp; I feel very thankful for the point interests me much &amp; may throw light on a very obscure problem.<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
<p>I trust to you to be so good as to let me hear as soon as you have any information.</p>
<p>Many thanks for M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Glenie’s excellent letter, to whom I have written by this post to return my thanks for his kindness.<ref target="#foot.f3"/></p>
<p>With all good wishes believe me | my dear Thwaites | yours very sincerely | Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
            
        </div>

        

        

